review:
This was probably one of the best hotels I have ever stayed at, especially for a major city. I am so so happy we chose this hotel over some other options in the more touristy areas. 
- The area is wonderful. No, it's not what many guidebooks will recommend for first-time tourists to San Francisco, but I PROMISE it is better than staying in Fisherman's Wharf or Union Square. The area feels really safe, is super close to ANY public transit you could need (it's literally just outside the door), and is a wonderful place to walk around and explore, with many nice restaurants and coffee shops. Could not say better things about the area for a traveler. 
- The hotel itself is very impressive. The lobby is beautiful and the elevators are beautiful and exciting! They were working on a gorgeous Christmas display while we were there. 
- The room was large especially for a city, very clean, and we fortunately booked a room with a balcony, and OMG, what an amazing view. 
I highly recommend staying here for visits to San Francisco!

review: What is there not to like about the HYATT. It is always a wonderful hotel to stay at. My wife fell in love with the balcony with the bay view room. It is the only one we get. The staff are warm and welcoming from the valet drivers outside/entrance greeters are friendly,funny and professional. Every question i had they were mainly the ones to answer it for me. The front desk service had great customer service. They greeted me with a warm welcome to the establishment and because it was valentines day they had a beautiful red rose for my lady and champagne in the room. It made my wife feel special that day which they did all of it. Walking to my room I was even greeted by one of the service men. We had a little chat with laughter at the end, he saw me and my wife kind of struggling with our suitcases and even offered to help. I thought that was genuine for a worker that probably didn't even get paid to that job. So for the managers to the people in charge/owners of the facility. The front desk workers are awesome, but give a BIG notice and thank you to your workers that probably don't get the love and respect they should. And that is your frontline/entrance workers with amazing attitudes and knowledge for us/guest. The workers that are in the back stage that keep the place clean and in working order maid/handyman. They alone would be one reason I would come back to this hotel. Which I have numerous of times. So I hope you do something special for those workers that don't get the recognition that they deserve. Thank you all staff members for making my wife's valentines day one for the books. Facebook/Instagram friends and family wifes will be jealous on this one. Thank you for making me look like the dopest husband this year. Now tell your boss to throw you a LITTLE SOMETHING 😉 💰

acommodation: Habitación con cama extragrande.
review: Sehr großes, modern eingerichtetes, sauberes Zimmer mit Panoramafenster. Blick war zur Market-Street und auf die Bay-Bridge (12. Stock). Bett war King-size mit vier großen Kopfkissen. Neben normalen Lampen gibt es ein Ambient-Light über dem Bett. Toll: Wenn man nachts im Dunkeln aufsteht, registriert ein Sensor unter dem Bett die Bewegungen und es aktiviert ein kleines Licht unter dem Bett (aber nur auf der Seite, wo man aufgestanden ist), sodass man nirgendwo anstößt. Das Bad und die Dusche sind sehr groß, sauber und sehr gut beleuchtet. Das Hotel-Atrium, die 'Außenlifte' und der Blick von dort sowie von den einzelnen Etagen (immerhin 17) auf den 'Innenhof' ist sehr beeindruckend. Man sollte aber keine Höhenangst haben.

acommodation: King Studio Suite with Accessible Tub - Disability Access
review:
I did not like the lack of attention to the elevator. It was down for two days, which allowed for only one elevator. This hotel is very busy, and having one elevator was inconvenient. But, I can live with that. 
What really sent me to a boil is a guest below decided to disregard the one courteous rule of pretty much EVERY hotel in the world—smoking!! The signs are all over the place, even marked on the slider towards the balcony and, yes, even ON the balcony! So, the disgusting plume of smoke wafted in my room above him. 
But, this is the redeeming part: I called the front desk, they promptly—I mean promptly— called the room and told the tenants that smoking is prohibited in the rooms and that there are designated smoking areas outside the hotel. Furthermore, they called me back and said if they continued, they would be told to leave! 
No more smoke for the remainder of my stay and I got to enjoy the fresh air from the balcony. 
Now, that’s service!!!

Furthermore, the staff’s lack of responsiveness was a significant issue, and i felt that sometime that they need to learn how to act nice.
Adding to my dissatisfaction was the lack of parking facilities for guests. There were no on-site parking options, and I had to resort to a nearby parking lot, which charged an exorbitant fee of nearly $40 per night. The distance between the parking lot and the hotel was quite a walk, making it inconvenient, especially when carrying luggage or returning late in the evening. review: The hotel feels like it was a great place to stay back in the 90s, but hasn't seen much maintenance nor updates since then. The lobby is the only part that was renovated. Some elevators were out of business, the valet parking service was not functioning, and there were no staff to help with luggage upon arrival. The room itself was apparently clean but really worn out, lighting was missing and the balcony door might as well be kept open because closing it would not make much of a difference in weather and sound insulation.

review:
Es ist relativ weit ab vom Schuss und in SFO ist es sehr schwer sich via Uber etc. fortzubewegen, es sei denn man möchte viel Geld ausgeben :D Wir hatten also jedes Mal einen ca. 30 minütigen Fußweg zum Pier 39 und Fisherman’s Wharf. 
Die Straße beim Hotel ist sehr laut und man hört sie noch deutlich in den Zimmern. Das sollte man sich bei Buchung bewusst sein und ggf. Ohropax parat haben, wenn man da empfindlich ist wie ich :) 
Wir hatten extra um ein ruhiges Zimmer gebeten und dafür auch extra bezahlt, allerdings nützte das nichts. Außerdem war direkt unter unserem Zimmer eine Bar, die einen Abend wirklich extrem laut war. Gott sei Dank wurde sie aber um 22:00 Uhr geschlossen, sodass es uns nicht die ganze Nacht wachhielt. Das sind aber Faktoren, die das Hotelpersonal nicht beeinflussen kann :)
